criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Men and women greater than or equal to 18 years of age;

          -  A mean baseline platelet count between 50 × 10^9/L and <100 × 10^9/L;

          -  Participant is scheduled to undergo operations to critical sites (eg, eye surgery,
             neurosurgery) or operations with a high risk of bleeding (eg, major abdominal
             surgery), and, in the opinion of the Investigator, would otherwise require a platelet
             transfusion aiming for a platelet count of at least 100 × 10^9/L to prevent bleeding

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Participant with a history of arterial or venous thrombosis;

          -  Participant plans to have a platelet transfusion or plans to receive blood products
             containing platelets within 7 days of the Screening Visit;

          -  Use of anticoagulant or antiplatelet therapy;

          -  Use of erythropoietin-stimulating agents;

          -  Participant has a known medical history of genetic prothrombotic syndromes; or

          -  Participant has abnormal hemoglobin levels or prothrombin time/international
             normalized ratio
